content:
The trip plan has been designed to meet all constraints: visiting all five cities for the specified durations, adhering to the direct flight connections, and satisfying the time windows for Geneva and Munich. The total trip duration is 17 days, with the stay durations summing to 21 days, but accounting for 4 inter-city moves where transition days are shared, resulting in 17 calendar days.

- Geneva is visited first for 4 days (days 1-4), ensuring the relatives are visited between day 1 and day 4.
- Munich is visited next for 7 days (days 4-10), ensuring the friends are met between day 4 and day 10.
- Bucharest is visited for 2 days (days 10-11).
- Valencia is visited for 6 days (days 11-16).
- Stuttgart is visited last for 2 days (days 16-17).

The direct flight connections are:
- Geneva to Munich (direct flight)
- Munich to Bucharest (direct flight)
- Bucharest to Valencia (direct flight)
- Valencia to Stuttgart (direct flight)

